Taurus Security System (TSS)Taurus family of semi-auto pistols all feature the Taurus Security System, which provides instant-ready defense with built-in ability to secure your pistol and make it inoperable at the turn of a key. When the Security System is engaged, the pistol cannot be fired or cocked and the gun's manual safety cannot be disengaged. As with our revolver Security System, the device is part of the firearm and cannot be lost, and the same special Security Key works for both the revolver and pistol Systems (two keys come with most guns). To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun. Transfer BarThe transfer bar mechanism prevents the hammer from striking the firing pin unless the trigger is pulled fully to the rear.

title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer SSG 3000
postcontent: I have a sig ssg 3000 rifle for sale. This model is the origional ssg 3000 rifle that came from germany and has the mcmillam stock, not the new cheaper plastic stock that later came on the ssg rifles. These first production rifles are hard to find now, and both the older and newer model are no longer shipped to or made available to the United States. The mcmillan stocks that came on the first models were about $900 in themselves. The newer ssg 3000 rifles also have a 0-moa cant base intergrated in the action, where the origional ssg rifles could be fitted with a 20moa base for extra elevation adjustment. This rifle will come with the 20moa base. Rifle has around 300 rounds down the barrel and is in great shape. It will also include a heavy duty gun-guard hard case, one magazine and a field size gun cleaning kit. The triggers on these rifles feel a lot like that of a sako trg 22/42,excellent. The magazine is longer than average, so if you hand load, you can seat heavy high BC bullets out to the lands/rifling and still magazine feed them. Remington, winchester, savage and most other style rifles chambered in .308 would be limited by the maximum internal magazine length, on how far you can seat the heavies out. Scope, rings and bipod are not includedin the sale. The price is firm. Not interested in trades. Call or text: two five one four two two five four seven two.
